comment: Dr. Hipp is great. She is very caring and understanding. She is willing to make extensions on homework if you're overloaded with other work or personal issues. Homework is fairly easy. ratingTags: Respected--Get ready to read--Caring

comment: Hipp is such a good teacher she made me dislike all other English teachers I've had since. She would put so much time of her own aside to make your papers the best they could be. ratingTags: Gives good feedback--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Caring

comment: Gwinner is a great teacher. Most english students love him (and get his jokes). I felt so bad for him when he taught history and no one got his jokes. He is a easy grader and cool to be around. just has a weird sense of humor.

I believe the focus should be more on history itself rather than English and grammar. Ever paper was picked apart and I'm a pretty competent writer.

He is a difficult grader but you can tell he reads your papers and cares about what you write and will reward you if you put in the effort. Has annoying "cetween grades" system. Has a real subtle sarcastic sense of humor about the books he teaches which can appear without warning.

People that are saying negative things about him have low comprehension levels &don't enjoy thinking for themselves. He challenges you to be the best you can be &that means he doesn't give out easy A's. Plus, he is hilariously sarcastic. If you are lazy and ignorant, stay clear of his classes because they will not be ideal thriving grounds for you.

comment: He's very experienced, and knowledgable about what he's teaching. His powerpoint are detailed so you don't HAVE to read the chapters but you'll definitely get more information that way. Typically lets you know what will be on the exams so that helps too. Is generally also open to feedback if you have an issue in the course.

comment: Phelps knows what he is talking about. He has many years in the area of group work for being a social worker. Will learn lots from him! Expect a lengthy 10 page paper that will be a long process, so start ASAP. Really enjoyed his class!!
Really in the field for all the right reasons. I had to work pretty hard but I learned a lot. Don't show lack of participation, and do the reading. He offers extra credit.
Amazing
Academically has high expectations, which is good. Something about his attitude is off putting though. Learned enough but wouldn't take his class again.
One of my best professors. Expects students to work but will take time to go above and beyond to help.  Gives an E.C paper that can raise up to an entire grade level!

Very knowledgeable and passionate about material he is teaching. If you study for the tests you will do fine.  This class requires two extensive assignments, but if you do quality work, he will grade you fairly.

Phelps can be intimidating but is actually a very nice guy.  I got a A in the class.  I never used the book, did the paper the week it was due and got a high B.  He really cares about his work and his students.  Just pay attention and participate and you will do well.  Dont stress over his grading or the book.
great prof, really gets u prepared but you better be willing to work for your grade

uses turn it in, hard teacher, tests that cover readings, requires meeting in the center for teaching and learning, long paper (10+) dont take if you want an easy class. you will probably learn alot, he is a very nice laid back guy that will work with you.

Shares his personal experiences as a social worker, both good and bad, this made him more human. I found his lectures to be useful. If you follow the syllabus, ask questions, participate, and read the chapters you will do fine.
This professor is a very hard paper grader aand he is not willing to work with you.
Excellent instructor; really believes in what he's teaching

Really good professor. Asks a lot of his students and offers a challenging class. Personable but a very very tough grader. If you struggle with paper writing, get help before you have him grade a paper!
Interesting lectures; difficult tests; tough grader

Super easy, and very helpful. There's no due dates for papers, just preferred dates. as long as you get them in by the end of the semester, take part in conversations, and READ the few pages he assigns it's a free A. GPA booster all day. Extremely nice and goes out f his way to help, even if writes the paper for you. Yes, you read that right. GREAT
Overly helpful professor. Due dates on papers were not always enforced just time recommendations. Class can be dry and boring due to lengthy lectures and the professor tends to stray off topic.

He is my favorite teacher at AU, love him! He always made time to email me or talk to me if I needed help and even encouraged it! The class is a lot of deep discussion and some stuff is over your head, especially with the essays...but he is very, very, very helpful so it makes it easy. I would highly suggest him as a teacher!

Scott was by far the best math teacher i've had. He is very clear and is willing to work with you and help you on any questions you have. Before any exam, he has study sessions that are great help! Wish he taught all of my needed math classes.

Very good prof. answers any questions you have and he has study sessions before an exam. He lets you use you notes and hw on tests. He keeps class interesting sometimes he crack a couple jokes about some people but not in a bad way. If you hate math and want an easy class to take i would definitely recommend taking his class very very HELPFUL!

Dr. Scott is an amazing teacher. He makes math easy to understand without boring you with his wit and how he approaches problems. I wish he could teach all of the math class I am going to be takingi n the future! He made me realize that I don't need to be good at math but if I work hard it'll pay off and I can get the grade I want.
Mr. Scott is immoral, ridiculous, and very demeaning. He makes fun of students and makes everybody uncomfortable. He does a horrible job, and I will never take a class of his again.

I have a knack for math anyway, but Professor Scott really makes it easy for students to know what it is that they're doing wrong, and how to fix it. He lets you ask questions on homework and fix it before you even turn it in! It's great!

i had this man for college algebra. the first day i thought the class was gonna blow because i suck at math. but jim is an amazing teacher. very understanding and offers help left and right. he WANTS you to not only know HOW but why you are doing what you do. and he has a wicked sense of humor.
He is such a great professor!! He likes to relate to each and every student.. and he wants you to succeed!
Lets you use all notes you take on every test..homework is major part of grade..allowed 4 absences..very easy to retake tests..old school teacher with a very wide range of sense of humor
He is a great teacher, but you have to have a open mind he cares about how you do so make sure if you are having problems you talk to him!

Peds - Lecture was not helpful, but don't skip class, she gives good reviews in prep for tests. The book is an easy read, although the format will annoy you, it is what you need to do well (just read it!). Horrible tests (questions are not always straight forward, most are made to trick you, but she gives points back if most people get them wrong).
I thought Professor Sommers was a great instructor and a great person as well! She was very sweet and helpful if I had questions or just needed to talk.

She is 50/50 on her responsiveness, but overall a good teacher.  This is nursing school and if you expect to learn everything you are tested on from a lecture, then you don't belong in the program.  She is a bit scattered but makes boring topics interesting.

Okay, guys. It's nursing school - of course you have to read the book. Sommers is a beautiful person & a wonderful teacher. She went out of her way to help me out, not b/c I was her favorite (she didn't know who I was), but rather b/c she really cares about her students. Be an adult, show up to class, READ THE CHAPTERS (durh!), and you'll be fine!

She is nice, but not a good teacher. No one felt like they were prepared for her exams. She made it seem like if you came to class, you could do well on the exams. READ THE BOOK. She doesn't grade papers fairly, either. She is very hard to get a hold of. Don't expect her to answer your questions or emails. Nice as a person, if she likes you...
Mrs. Sommers is so nice! I can't believe the reviews she got!!!

she does not teach the material effectively and will not spend indvidual time with her students. she is not only nasty and ruthless, but she does not teach us.she is horrible grader and no one likes her. that might soud mean,but this women is seriously horrible. and she looks exacly like this
Worst instructor ever. Unprepared for class. Doesn't follow through on anything. Never responds to emails. DO NOT TAKE HER FOR ANYTHING.
by FAR worst teacher/professor I have ever had. She plays favorites and grades to what SHE likes and not the quality of work.
poor teacher, her lecture are very boring and useless,nobody like her except herself
terrible teacher and clinical instructor,cant teach without books,never good prepered for lecture
VERY POOR TEACHER.NOBODY LIKE HER

Professor Sommers couldn't teach her way out of a paper bag if her life depended on it.  She is a VERY nice woman and she will help you if you go to her.  But in the classroom she just can't teach.  Be prepared to be very confused.

Great professor.  likes to see her students succed.  caring, helpful; don't judge her by the way her syllabus, she is abid to follow School of Nursing's rules.  Let her know if you need help and she will take care of you.  Don't get on her bad side (just like any other person, don't expect someone to be nice to you if you are not nice to them).  BT

Good Teacher, Helpful (only teacher that i know in the whole program that i actually cares about student success, that i noticed)  She tries to use different materials from multiple sources to help us better understand the concept.  Overall i recommend her
i love dr. kennedy's class. my favorite so far this year!
She is the best. Period. End of story.

Dr. Kennedy is probably the best teacher on campus. Her government class is really interesting, because she used to work in government so she really knows what she's talking about. Also, she keeps lectures current (this week was about ISIS in Paris). I have tried to register for more of her classes (PSC, IDS or anthro), but they're always full!

I don't know what the last reviewer was talking about when he said that Dr. Kennedy's government class was awful. I (& many other students in the class) LOVED it! Yes, she taught government from a cultural perspective, but that made her class interesting, because government is about PEOPLE. When I see powerpoints, I think "lazy teacher!" Not her!!

She is an anthropolist, not a government professor. Unless you understand government, maybe you could understand what she is talking about. But there is no power points, the quizzes are essay style, and she does not respond to emails. Ugh this class was a nightmare for everyone.
Dr. Kennedy is the best teacher at AU!
Dr. Kennedy is a great teacher and keeps ever class lively. All of her lectures are clear and easy for everyone to follow. I would definitely recommend taking this course with her.

Professor Kennedy does an exceptional job at encouraging students to think outside of the box and to not be afraid of sharing one's opinion. Professor Kennedy goes above simply 'following the course material' because she shows that she actually cares about students being individuals and able to make decisions regarding how they view the world.
AWESOME prof -- i absolutely LOVE Dr. Kennedy!
All I can say is: take any class Dr. Kennedy teaches! She is the absolute BEST teacher at AU!!!!!!!

i just finished my 2nd class with dr. kennedy and (again) it was my favorite! i'm almost sorry that I'm graduating... she's the best thing about AU -- by FAR!! i learned more from her than any 2 profs combined. TAKE HER CLASS!!!

Awesome professor! She respects everyone's personal opinion and even encourages it. She makes class fun and sometimes talks about her personal life in relation to the material which I can appreciate. I was shocked at how much I learned and enjoyed from a class I had no interest in taking in the first place. Great! I recommend Cultural Anthropology.
TAKE DR. KENNEDY'S ANTHROPOLOGY CLASS. YOU'LL LOVE IT!!!!! I WISH I HAD HER FOR ALL OF MY CLASSES. THE BEST PROF AT AU, HIGHLY RECOMMENDED.

I'm in Dr. Kennedy's Global Justice class & it's my FAVORITE! It's at 8am, but Dr. Kennedy is so smart, funny & interesting, we have so much fun! We're raising $$$ for charities by selling T's, face painting & making balloon hats. Once we spent half the class practicing face painting & making balloon hats! Who lets you do that in a class?? GREAT!!!

Dr. Kennedy IS liberal (as one student wrote), but she definitely does NOT push her "agenda." She not only listens to other opinions (respectfully), but actively encourages them! During the first weeks of class, she told us that it was the "responsibility" of us Conservatives to "check her" if she got too radical. She is a FANTASTIC teacher!

i started dr. kennedy's class with no interest in cultural anthropology, & thought i'd be an easy "a." well, i sure changed my mind! 1. i loved the class, even though it was a lot harder than i thought it would be. 2. i can't believe how much i learned! and 3. i discovered the BEST professor at AU, who REALLY knows her stuff! Take ALL her classes!!
Dr. Kennedy's anthropology class is probably one of the hardest I've ever taken -- but I LOVED it! I learned so much and plan to take more classes from this great teacher. HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!!!!!

Deb is the epitome of a professor that loves what she does. Energetic, hilarious, fair, and clear. Papers are on the heavier side but she gives you options as to which papers you want to write. Extremely liberal and likes to push her political agenda (but that's college). She's an amazing lady and one of the best professors I have had.

it's been said by others on this ratings site, but i'll say it again -- dr. kennedy is the best prof i EVER had! i'm taking another class from her this spring. tough course material, but she makes it fun to come to class! VERY HIGHLY recommended!

simply AMAZING. she is the epitome of what every college professor should be like. crystal clear lectures that makes the material seem easy. also explains reasoning behind the problem, which helps you comprehend the material better. i'm graduating soon, so know i will never have another prof like her again.

Dr. Deb loves teaching & it shows. Loves her students & it shows. Knows what she's talking about & it shows. Very classy lady & treats all of her students with respect. I highly recommend this prof!!!
It's only week #1 & I LOVE Dr. Kennedy! Her class is already my favorite -- exciting, engaging, interesting & controversial. What's not to love??? HIGHLY RECOMMENDED
You can really tell she loves her job -- very enthusiastic about the material and knows what she is talking about. Very engaging. Tough but fair, and very helpful. A great professor.
Dr. Kennedy's class is great. Learned so much & had fun, too! I'll be taking as many classes from her as I can. Highly recommended!!!
VERY smart, but down to earth. I learned a lot & had fun too! What else can I say? Deb's the BEST!
TAKE HER CLASS -- TRULY PHENOMENAL PROFESSOR!
Deb is the BEST professor at AU. She's smart, funny and interesting, and REALLY knows what she's talking about! I changed my major because of her & plan to take as many of her classes as I can :-)

Very liberal, entertaining woman. she teaches an interesting class, had her for 3. 1 small assignment per week in all. 1 longer paper. (7-12 depending on class) tests are EASY- she gives u the questions prior to tests. you will learn and be entertained. shes fun and down to earth. very smart- highly reccomended.
Deb is very smart and her class is very interesting.  She knows how to relate to her students and have a good time.  She is laid back and keeps things interesting.  Recommended!!
She's fun and I enjoy my (four hour night) class with her, so I recomend her.

i have her for cultural anthropology. interesting teacher, swears a lot but is friendly. i'm not too interested in the class but she's always telling stories and jokes so that makes the class entertaining.
My FAV class!! She's smart, funny, & I learned a lot. Her classes are a must at AU!=)
Awesome teacher . hands down.

Professor Zelman is just simply awesome. He's such a nice man and is super nerdy but funny. He's always willing to help you out but you will most likely not need the extra help because he explains things in class so well. He's my favorite professor at AU so far! very organized !

Dr. Zelman is a great teacher! I highly reccomend him. The topic is not easy but he explains it very clearly and he is always willing to help a student if they don't understand. He gives 10 quizes throughout the semester and takes your top 5 scores to out in the grade book. If I could take him again, I definitely would!

Dr. Zelman is a great professor. he gets a bit off subject, and loves his pictures, but that is ok. He is very understanding and if you need help just ask. If i got the chance to be in a class with him again, I would get in. Awesome teacher
Awesome professor! Dr. Zelman is always very nice and his classes are very interesting.
No Comments

Dr Bejec was very unclear thoughout the course. Her grading method is very confusing, and she barely taught us the material, she wasn't very patient with the class. I tried approaching her for help and she would forcefully do it. Nice person, but I wouldn't take a course with her again.
She was such a great professor. Loved every class. I came early and she taught me extra chemistry!
Good teacher but treats you like a 5 year old.
Great teacher, fun, humors, good stories.  Very easy teacher.  Just show up, do your work and you will get an A.
Dr. Bejec is a fantastic professor! She is professional, humorous, accomodating, enthusiastic, and a great role model.

Prof Escobedo assigns a lot of readings-they are to be used as sources to your essay assignments. READ THEM. She gives a lot of days off to comp for museum assignment. ratingTags: Get ready to read--Participation matters--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: I took her for art history, and she only reads off her powerpoints that are available online. You don't need to read the textbook, or even buy it. I watched Netflix the entire time and got an A
ratingTags: Tests? Not many--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Easiest college professor God, or Allah or the big bang put on this planet. I went to class once a week, used google on the final and still got a B in the class. Just do the stuff she gives you and average a C on the tests/final and you're GUARUNTEEEEED a B.

I had both Art History classes with her. I was never interested in this area of study but it is now going to be my major! I loved every class. She also pointed out the humor in art. The tests aren't too hard even though a lot of my classmates did poorly, you just have to pay attention in class.
Easy teacher. Never any homework. You actually have to try to fail in her class.

I don't know what professor you all are referring to but she is the worse. Taking her for online dimensions and we only had a handful of live lectures. comment: Amazing professor. Had her the first semester of nursing school and almost wish i didnt because she set the bar so high for other teachers. She keeps lectures interesting, but MAKE SURE YOU READ, that book is your bible for that class. Miss her, i dont think she knows who I am but i respect her so much as a teacher, nurse, and person
ratingTags: Respected--Get ready to read--Amazing lectures

comment: Great instructor and lecturer . I could sit and listen to entire lecture and not be bored. Wonderful nurse. Pay attention and book is a necessity.

comment: Professor Novak was definitely the better choice for 3260. The lectures can be dry at times but she keeps the class lively with her sarcastic humor. ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Respected--Get ready to read

comment: Mrs. Novak is definitely the better choice over Garcia for 3260. If something specific is on the test, she WILL tell you. She doesn't waste her time teaching useless material, so soak everything in. Lectures can be boring, I recommend sitting in the front because she talks soft sometimes. She is a very helpful instructor if you respectfully ask.

OB - There are things said in class that are not in her PP that will be on the test. I didn't find her lectures helpful. Read the book! OB tests are mostly knowledge based. Too much info though to cram into 8 weeks. I felt like I was on my own. If you don't do the required reading before the semester starts, you'll be met with an "oh well" attitude
This is the nurse I want taking care of me if I'm ever in the hospital. She's extremely knowledgeable, nothing slips by her, and she's hot.
Loved her! She comes off tough on the first day- don't be scared, shes really kind and helpful! She knows the information backwards and forwards. I can't wait to have her again for OB!
She's awesome! Extremely helpful and always makes time if you have any questions!

Novak is an excellent instructor. Her powerpoints are great, her lectures are great, and she's just really great at teaching. I'm glad I didn't have her for lab though, for some reason, I find her a little intimidating =)

Mrs. Novak is by far the best nursing teacher at AU. Her PowerPoints are extremely helpful and made by her personally. She is straight to the point, her lectures reflect her test. I highly recommend her!
Great, caring teacher.  Her lectures are very helpful.  She is always willing to help.
Novak is an amazing professor. She is so passionate about what she does. She is tough but that is nursing. Take her! You will learn!!!!!
Suzanne is one of the best professors at AU.  She is a great teacher.  Her power points are clear and right to the point.  I highly recommend her.
nice and caring person and teacher. her class is fun, but not that easy. good luck.

Worst teacher I have ever had. She reads straight from the book, has no idea what she's talking about, and is completely disorganized. She is not clear about what is on her tests and makes what could be an interesting class completely miserable. If possible, don't ever take this class with her.

This teacher read us the slides and was very tangential.  When I was having trouble and went to her for help she told me a C was a good grade then said to practice nclex exams in preparation for her tests.  She might be very smart and have a nice personality but teaching is just not her thing. Have fun guessing what to study, Klein was WAY better.

She goes through lectures really quickly but what do you expect from a nursing class? All teachers usually do. Her tests are NOT that hard but you do need to study, make drug cards, GO TO CLASS, & read the book. She makes pharm interesting & I preferred her over Klein any day or place. She could change her grading though & add an assignment ...

Very very good teacher. She knows what she is talking about, and is really into what she teaches making classes not as boirng as others. Show that you are a hard worker and study you will do fine, i recommend her highly
very selfish -- in stage *.....i know......* lecture are long and not intresting--time wasting.Better when she give up and get out  from teaching wrrrrrrr

Laura is a phenomenal professor.  She knows everything!  She's tough and the class is hard but if you study and ask her for help you'll make it.  She really cares about her students.  Definitely a favorite of mine, I'd take anything she teaches.

I didn't have any problems with this instructor until the 3rd test. One miscommunication  and she cost a lot of students a letter grade. I'm still a little sore from it. Not sure if she did it on purpose or not. If multiple instructors teach the same class, to be safe, go to all of them to find out what material is going to be covered on the tests!

I like Mrs. LoVerde! She's really sweet and willing to help you if you ask her. Class is just reading from the powerpoints but I dont know what more could be done.. the class is hard but she doesn't make the tests.
She does not want you to do well. She likes to make you feel unprepared. She doesn't test you on what she taught. Horrible Teacher!

I learned so much in this class. Ms Watson is the best teacher I have had at AU so far. She teaches then tells why she does it that way and gives examples of how we can apply her teaching in our own classrooms. GREAT INSTRUCTOR!

I just called Kathy at home at 7:30 because of missing class with a health concern, and I never called in cause i was in the emergency room.  She was so kind, compassionate,Then waived my assignment due dates. We made an appt. for me to get caught up. She made me feel like a boulder was lifted off of me. She is the best MATC prof I've had.

Very expensive books, and most you use for just 1 assignment.  Kathy's probably the best MATC professor at AU.  She allows students the freedom to structure lessons their own way, and comes prepared w/ printed notes for students each class.  I'd highly recommend taking her class!
Turned in a huge project. She went through every single section, page, paragraph and sentence. Got an A, but found out by her comments can't BS way through anything. She will find it!

This is a tough class with a lot of work. Schedule it for when you aren't taking 2 other classes. Books are expensive. Professor Watson is AWESOME! She teaches, doesn't lecture, will help you with anything. Make sure she is the instructor when you take this course. She will help you become a great teacher- best class in the MATC program!
Lots of work, and her book list for the class rings up at almost $500!!  No joke.
Great Teacher.  She knows what she is talking about and is extremely considerate of each student.  Take her class if you can.

One of the most talented professors I ever had. Kathy is an expert in Literacy Methods. She plans everything well and class is never boring. We were provided lots of info to help when we start teaching. The class is difficult, but Kathy mixes theory with practical application, we know why it is important to learn the content. Best class at AU ever.

All I can say is "WOW"! I was dreading this course because I heard it was hard and a lot of work. However, Kathy is always willing to help and will return emails and lets you call her anytime when you need help on a project. I learned more from her than any other professor- she actually teaches rather than lecture Take her class.

Kathy is a talented teacher and extremely knowledgeable. Her expertise and experience as a school principal really made the course come alive for me! LOVE to hear her stories from the field! She is very, very picky about work being correct and BEST PRACTICE. But, she will let you re-do an assignment without penalty and help you do it correctly.

LOVE LOVE LOVE JACKSON. Have had him for 3 classes already over the course of two years. He is by far the best professor I have ever had. He truly cares for all his students and has amazing lectures. If you put in the effort, you'll get an easy A. I highly recommend him!

He is amazing! He takes the time to get to know each of his students and treats them with respect. There are not many quizzes and he grades very fair on our papers. He makes class interesting and not many people skipped. Loved it

I had Dr. Jackson for a few weeks after the midterm. He had to have a quadruple bypass and was replaced. This was disappointing. Although his class was boring, he was so laid back and easy. Easy grader and had few assignments.
knows material and willing to help.  will challenge you to take learning risks
He wasnt helpful and the class was BORING!!!

He teaches you a lot about different tools you can use in the classroom and does a lot of fun group projects that you can use in class. There was not a lot of work and he was a nice guy. I did feel like I didn't learn enough about the science aspect of the class though.

Rob's dedication to the social work field is evident in the classroom. He does not sugar coat the reality of the job, but reinforces the reasons behind why we do what we do, to get the BEST possible outcome for our clients. It's an honor to learn from this passionate social worker!
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Respected--Amazing lectures

comment: I took Castillio class back in spring 2015. I was recommended to take his class but will CERTAINLY NOT recommend him. I felt he degraded me based on my writing skills.

Professor Castillo really cares about his students. He wants to make sure your reaching your full potential and that your getting the most of the class. He has a lot of experience working in the addictions field of social work and he applies this in class. He is always there for advice and feedback. He's a great professor!!

Professor Castillo was always very accommodating and understanding. He demonstrated perfectly his knowledge and experience of the field we were discussing, unlike many professors in the school's Social Work program, and made the class straightforward with the information we were taught and would need (for tests and for our future careers).

I took Professor Castillo for a drugs & human behavior class. He is highly experienced in his field & knowledgeable. He makes you feel comfortable to ask any questions & class discussion is great. His tests are not difficult & gives a time period in the middle of exams to look at your study guide. Group projects were used & many papers assigned.

This professor absolutely knows what he is talking about in regard to mental health and diagnosing.  He is also easy to understand and follow in class.  I believe that he wants you to succeed and he teaches in a way that encourages you to stay interested and learn the material.  I enjoyed his class and would take him again if I could.
Didn't follow syllabus. Didn't complete syllabus. Grades papers fairly. Tests can be tricky.
He is great! He keeps the material interesting and he is passionate about his field. He is inspiring and fair. He cares about everyone equally.

He is a hard professor to understand! He says one thing about an assignment but changes his mind without letting others know. Thinks he is a good paper expert when he doesn't know much about APA style. Would not take any of his courses again unless he is the ONLY one teaching it.

Prof. Castillo is a very talented clinician. I took his course at the master's level. I was impressed with his dedication and commitment to our learning experience. He is not only effective as a professional, but also as an educator. He is an asset to the Social Work program. His ability to challenge us in class make us better clinicians overall.

Don't try to get a better grade on a paper after his has given you your marks. Not recommended for an IDS teacher. Papers required to be long and when the papers are graded there was no rubric it was how he was feeling at that moment. Grade on papers have a lot to do with how well APA style is. Although he is no APA expert (he thinks he is however)
No Comments
Challenging tests, but the homework teaches well!
If you have the option to take it with another professor, DO NOT HESITATE!!! Goes to fast on material and does not review. His too cocky and does not care if you pass or fail!
Hes hot.

Dr. Ramirez is very knowledgeable on the topics he teaches in class. He is a little tough but if you take the time to understand the material either in class or during office hours he is very helpful.
Really good and class is not hard at all.  as long as you show up and pay some attention
Very Helpful. Makes the class fun and light. Loves his job and will make sure that you understand how to do things. As long as you attend class you will do fine on quizzes and tests.

He's an amazing math teacher, but at times comes off very full of himself. If you study & go to class you will do fine on quizes/tests. He's also very interested in your sucess as his student and mentions extra help often.
Incredibly organized. Someone you have to warm up to. Definite political opinions. Had some interesting discussions about current events. Would have liked to have had more of that.

Professor Windsor is very upfront with what she looks for when it comes to getting assignments done. I loved listening to her stories about certain experiences, because she has done so much in the Social Work field. Her papers were pretty easy, in my opinion. All tests were multiple choice, gotta know the information though, weren't too hard.

She is incredibly organized, but she has a few quirks. For example, she will share what her stereotypes are and I, for one, don't want to hear them.  If preconceived notions of populations are discussed, it should be done with the understanding that negative preconceptions should be changed.

She is an extremely helpful teacher, versatile in every way. This teach really loves her job, and her students! Be prepared for a lot of paper, but she is a fair grader and takes the time to iron out wrinkles!
Great teacher! Loved her class. Even at 9:20 in the morning it was interesting and the speakers were amazing!
She's great.  She's passionate about what she does and she's understanding of any confusion or questions students have.  I love her and can't wait to keep taking her classes!

They're super easy (if you've came to class), but if you miss a quiz, you're out of luck. He's super funny and realistic. He is also from England which is cool.

comment: Not really a bad guy, and he's educated. Never announces when quizzes will be. If you miss the first few minutes of class on an unannounced quiz day, you fail that quiz. comment: A great teacher and an even better friend. He is hilarious and really makes you look at things from a different perspective. He has traveled the world and uses the experiences he's had in his life to teach some incredible lessons about history and life itself.  I'm not even a history major, but I will always take classes by him if it's an option.

This man is the best teacher I have ever had.  He is a intelligent, funny British man who keeps class interesting.  He always has some sort of story relating to the discussion.  The class doesn't feel like work at all.  Take his class, I promise you won't regret it

One of the best teachers I've ever had in my life. Makes class interesting and engaging. Is able to facilitate conversation on controversial issues without having students get angry at one another. He is also hilarious. If you have a chance to take a class with him I highly recommend it.

Dr.Forward is an amazing instructor. He is passionate about the subject matter and just appears to be a walking Religion encyclopedia. He knows his stuff and is well-rounded in a number of areas. Love him!
Martin is very intelligent and savvy... I very much enjoyed his class and moreso enjoy his friendship.

Dr. Butcher is an interesting and fair teacher.  Her love and respect for the profession is readily apparent, and she offers help and constructive criticism. The guest speakers are a great resource, and the work is skill building and useful. She understands differences in preferences of format.

Constructivist based.  In class journals on class activities; PBL for key assessment; guest speakers and a field trip; flexible; approachable; currently teaches in a classroom.  Nice Professor & pretty good class.  No complaints!

Before taking this class I had a 4.0 GPA with only a few classes to go before graduation. But, because of her tyrannical grading, I barely passed this class. She never had a valid reason to mark off points on assignments; instead she would leave vague comments that were never helpful.  Worst professor I have ever had. She's a nightmare, honestly.

Horrible teacher! Obsessed with discussion posts and doesn't grade fairly. How do I have an A in all of my other classes but not this one? I'm fighting to keep a B because of the UNFAIR GRADING. I started this class with 30+ students, there is 6 now! If you see that you have this instructor DROP THE CLASS.

Professor is unorganized with presentation notes. No exams, nothing but papers, useless busy work. She would benefit from helping struggling students instead of insulting them by suggesting "college may not be the best idea for them." Strict professor, arbitrary grading, and her powerpoints were pointless. Overall, I do not recommend her at all.

She honestly is a pretty good teacher.  I say this because I had her as a freshman and she really teaches you and expects to get to that college level. There is a lot of notetaking but its worth it. I enjoy her analysis, its not overly boring and she likes input from students. She helps you if you ask her for it.  Make sure you attend class.

I had her at NIU. I can't believe the negative comments I am reading. THIS IS ONE OF THE BEST HISTORY PROFESSOR'S I HAVE EVER HAD. She is extremely knowledgeable, funny, intelligent, and GREAT at teaching/conveying information. She makes you work, but her class is rather easy if you show up, do what she asks, and put forth a little effort. 50/50!!!

By far the worst professor I have ever had. She is extremely inefficient at actually teaching anyone anything. She does not organize herself well and could afford to put a lot more effort into her curriculum. I do not recommend her as a professor...

She knows her stuff but is almost tyrannical when running a classroom. Our class got insulted and kicked out of class repeatedly.Her idea is to kick you out of class/call you stupid. Lets not try and inspire them or help them to learn...Overall, intelligent lady with a huge attitude who i could not wait to be free from.

I think Professor Lemus is an amazing teacher. I thank her for teaching me about the different views of controversial topics of history. I will graduate in 2012 with my degree in history. I hope to one day impact someone else as much as she has impacted me.

lectures are often boring, write a paper based on a text not discussed in class, group project, attendance grades, easy if youre a try hard student. can get away with minimal reading accept on papers. average workload. strict prof.

I'm a history major & I got a good grade, but she was the worst teacher I've ever had. She assigned group projects & asked us to do evals but said we'd be penalized if they didn't say the same thing. she was great! her lectures were pretty interesting, and if you needed help, you could email her and she would email back pretty much right away.  you need to work hard to get a good grade in the class, but she'll definitely help you out

One of the most entertaining profs ive had! Shes so funny and relatable! Just be prepared to do a lot of readings and actually discuss them but other than that the class is great! Jeopardy review before tests and extra credit! If you can, get her for one of your psych classes!

comment: She was so great when I had her! Definitely plan on taking more psych classes with her. PowerPoints are great, lectures are great, tests are straightforward and she spends time reviewing the material before each exam. Also gives out lots of extra credit! Shes very energetic too

comment: Talks very fast, but is very clear cut. All homework was online, one assignment a week usually very short. Did not take attendance at all. Gave out total of 50 extra credit points.

She's an Excellent Professor. She is very clear when lecturing and gives great examples. Her class isn't hard at all! You just have to show up to class, take notes and you'll pass.  Her tests are curved off the highest grade, so that's always a bonus. If something wasn't clear, she will explain in a different way until you understand.

This professor is the Disney princess of psychology professors; she's a very cute, energetic lady. With that being said she is a VERY hard grader and there were times when I didn't feel like my, or others, opinions were respected in her class. Dr. Spinos-Rudek is AWESOME! I love her way of teaching. My only regret is not taking her sooner as her PERSONALITY PSYCH class is the last of my psych minor. Very good instructor! would highly recommend!

Lots of info being told all at once dosnet make connections
